Being a notorious lead singer of a famous band didn't really affect Harry in any way- other than he got used to...
body:
Prancer | Harry Styles

— Moodboard

Being a notorious lead singer of a famous band didn’t really affect Harry in any way- other than he got used to girls chanting his name, making him grow a tinge of narcissistic nature, and he got used to showing off all of him.

It was his normal.

However, showing off would probably be the death of him.

“C'mon- just once around the rink!” Harry pleaded. He was standing on the ice, holding onto the barrier as he tried to coax the nurse to skate with him, at least once.

“I’m on duty,” She said, rolling her eyes. The smile that was clear on her face, however, just egged him on to continue.

He let out a dramatic sigh, his teeth finding his lips as he thought about his next move. She wasn’t even looking at him, her eyes were looking at the rink- waiting for any possible injuries.

“Not even as a Christmas present? I mean it is Christmas,” He tried again.

“What if someone gets hurt while I’m skating circles around you? What kind of doctor would I be?” She asked him, the smile not leaving her lips.

“Is that a challenge?” He asked, raising his right eyebrow as he stared the woman in front of him down.

“Not, just a fact.”

“Harry, you twat!” They both turned to look at the female voice that called. The doctor laughed as the splitting image of Harry came skating towards them- the doctor presumed that the woman was Harry’s sister. “You promised to skate with mum, it’s been nearly two hours and you didn’t yet!” She scolded, the man’s cheeks heated up, colouring a rosy colour.

He turned back to the woman, smirking and- purposely- popping his dimple out. “When does your shift end?” he asked her, to which she just shook her head.

“When the rink closes,” She shrugged. His face dropped, having too little time to respond as his sister dragged him away.

Harry did skate with his mum and the doctor couldn’t help but watch them, which caused her to be teased by the one nurse and two trainees that accompanied her to the event. She flipped them all off before excusing herself to the bathroom, trudging away in her skates.

One her way returning she saw Harry, no longer skating with his mum, but rather a small girl. He was holding her hand and when she wanted to skate on her own, he’d do all sorts of tricks. Prancing around the rink until she asked for his helping hand once more.

By the time she got back to the nursing station, he was picking her up and twirling her around as he spinned in a circle. He put her down, only to be asked to be picked up again. The doctor stood by the barrier’s gate, preparing for anything to go wrong because this couldn’t possibly go right.

And she was right, while Harry was spinning the girl, a boy accidentally skated into his front- sending him flying backwards.

Luckily, he gripped the girl to his chest and the boy had moved away from him just in time to not be hurt.

The doctor quickly skated towards the man, dodging the other skaters as effectively as possible.

As she got closer she heard Harry asking the girl if she was okay, to which she replied that she was uninjured. The doctor was relieved.

“How about you, Harry?” The doctor asked, coming to a halt near him.

“My arm hurts,” He pouted. The doctor nodded before helping the little girl off of his chest. Harry’s sister had come to the scene and took the girl from the doctor.

One of the trainees had come to help, the doctor warned about the arm before they both pulled Harry to his feet.

The doctor gripped him tightly as he was bound to have some blood rushing to his head. His eyes screwed shut and she took it as a sign to hold still.

“I’ve got him, just check on the girl,” She instructed the trainee- who only nodded before skating away.

“I think my arm’s broken,” Harry said, slowly opening his eyes. The doctor couldn’t help the quick breath intake at the sight of his eyes. They were absolutely beautiful, sparkling bright green eyes.

“Right, let’s go treat you then,” The doctor smiled moving to his right side and slinging his arm around her neck.

She assisted him to the nursing station before sitting him down in one of the chairs. She carefully took off his coat, then unbuttoned his right sleeve. She tried to move his wrist, which made him wince.

“Sorry,” She said- a blush on her cheeks at the warmness of his hand.

She decided to unbutton his shirt, which caused him to blush when her fingertips brushed against his skin.

“A moth?” She asked confused, referring to the big tattoo on his stomach.

“A butterfly,” He corrected, “Supposed to represent what you do to me.”

“You’re such a flirt,” She told him, pushing the shirt over his shoulders.

“Says the woman who’s undressing me,” He said, smiling cheekily at her. She stopped her actions, looking at him before rolling her eyes.

“I need to remove your sleeve, and this looks expensive so I don’t really want to cut it, so I’m sorry if I hurt you,” She explained, to which he only nodded- preparing to assist her a little.

They both successfully removed his arm, only having a few winces of pain. She did the necessary injury assessing before she put his arm in a cast. All while talking to the ridiculously handsome man.

She giggled at the joke he made as she finished buttoning his shirt back.

“The agency is going to be pissed,” Harry sighed, not moving from the chair.

“The agency?” The doctor asked, packing everything she used away.

“Yeah- I’m in a band,” He said, she could see the narcissistic glint in his eyes- he was probably really proud of it.

“Yeah?”

“Yeah- maybe you’d like to come to the studio sometime?” He asked, cheeks glowing again.

“Normally I’d say no, but I think I’ll make an exception.”

“Really?” His eyes and smile widened.

“Yeah, why not? You obviously need someone to keep you upright- don’t you prancer?” She asked, joking with him.

“Prancer,” He snorted, seeing his mum and sister walking towards him.

summary: Early morning fluff w Mila, ceo!harry, and model!Y/N,ft.Anne
body:
Early morning fluff w Mila, ceo!harry, and model!Y/N,ft.Anne

____

Y/N yawned as she walked down the stairs barefoot, her hair messy, and only a white robe, with her name sewed into the right shoulder in gold (Harry had one that matched. They also had ones that said Mr.Styles and Mrs.Styles, those are Harry’s favorite.)

“Harry, baby, I-oh! Hello, Anne!”

Harry smirked over his shoulder as he made breakfast.

“Hi, love! Sorry! I was at an early mass and I figured I’d pop by!”

“Oh, it’s no problem! I’m glad you’re here, we love having you over,” she smiled, giving Anne a hug and a kiss. “Sorry I’m not properly dressed.”

“Oh please, love! It’s your house,” Anne laughed.

“What did you need, baby?” Harry asked.

“I just wanted to say, first of all, good morning to my husband,” she laughed, hugging him around his waist, from behind. She kissed his shoulder. “Did you sleep okay?”

“I did. Did you?”

Y/N nodded. “Now,” she spoke but Harry had turned around for a kiss. They kept it short and sweet, seeing as Anne was there. “I just wanted to remind you,” she was smiling now that she’d gotten her kiss. “That Mila has a doctor’s appointment later. Will you be coming with us?”

“I’ve got to check my schedule but I think I’ll be able to make it.”

“Okay. I’m gonna go wake her up so she can eat and get ready.”

“Okay,” he called.

She returned twenty minutes later, with her pouty, sleepy baby, cuddling into her mommy’s chest because she wanted to go back to bed.

“Mila, look who’s here, say hi to Nana,” Y/N cooed.

Mila whined, rubbing her face against the soft material of Y/N’s robe.

“She’s sleepy, sorry, Anne,” Y/N laughed.

“It’s alright,” Anne laughed but kissed Mila on the head anyway. “I love you, darling.”

“And I love you too,” Harry spoke, kissing her cheek. “Daddy loves his baby. Why is she sad?” He asked, pouting.

She didn’t speak, only stared at him with puppy eyes.

“You wanna come with dada?” Harry asked, holding his arms out for her.

She shook her head, making Y/N laugh loudly in victory. “She loves me more!” (Their ongoing debate that everyone knew about, therefore both Harry and Anne laughed.)

Harry gasped. “You no wanna come with dada? But that’ll make me cry,” he pouted.

Then he went on to pretend like he was crying.

Her head lifted from Y/N’s chest.

“This is cheating,” Y/N commented, but nevertheless wanted to see how things would play out.

“I want Mila to come with me,” he cried. “Come with dada, Lala,” he pretended to cry.

“Dada,” Mila seemed to coo, making her parents and Nana laugh. She reached out one hand then the other, and hugged him tight. “Dada,” she cooed again.

“You stay with dada?” Harry pouted.

“Dada,” Mila nodded.

“Good,” he pouted, kissing her lips. “You’re my baby. Not mummy’s.”

He stared at her for a minute, the love in his eyes and the admiration he had for his baby apparent to everyone in the room. “You eat eggies with Dada, now?” He spoke in his baby voice. “I made them boiled for you.”

“Eggies?” He asked her again.

“Dada?” She spoke.

“Yes, princess?”

“Dada!” She tapped his chest over and over with her chubby little hand.

“What?!” He shrieked with a laugh, although he knew she didn’t know what she was doing.

“You just want me attention, huh?” He kissed her cheek.
